  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol in Envoy is implemented through a layered architecture with both legacy and unified components:\n\n## Legacy Components (SotW and Delta)\n\n**GrpcSubscriptionImpl** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h) serves as the adapter from typed Subscription interface to untyped GrpcMux. It handles per-xDS API stats and logging.\n\n**GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.h) is the factory that creates subscriptions. It selects between two modes:\n  - SotW mode using legacy GrpcMuxImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h)\n  - Delta mode using NewGrpcMuxImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h)\n\nThe factory implementation (grpc_subscription_factory.cc) checks the runtime feature \"envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux\" to decide between the legacy implementations and unified template-based implementations.\n\n**GrpcMuxImpl (Legacy SotW)** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h) implements State-of-the-World xDS protocol using DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse messages.\n\n**NewGrpcMuxImpl (Delta)** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h) implements Delta xDS protocol using DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse messages. It manages subscriptions through DeltaSubscriptionState and uses a WatchMap for tracking resource interests.\n\n## Unified Template Architecture (Newer)\n\nThe newer, more maintainable architecture uses templates defined in the XdsMux namespace (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/):\n\n**GrpcMuxImpl Template** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h) is a template class parameterized by:\n  - S: SubscriptionState type (SotwSubscriptionState or DeltaSubscriptionState)\n  - F: SubscriptionStateFactory type\n  - RQ: xDS request type (DiscoveryRequest or DeltaDiscoveryRequest)\n  - RS: xDS response type (DiscoveryResponse or DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n\nThis template is instantiated as:\n  - **GrpcMuxSotw**: Specializes for SotwSubscriptionState and DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse\n  - **GrpcMuxDelta**: Specializes for DeltaSubscriptionState and DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse\n\n**Subscription State Implementations** in xds_mux/:\n  - **SotwSubscriptionState** (sotw_subscription_state.h) with SotwSubscriptionStateFactory: Handles State-of-the-World protocol state\n  - **DeltaSubscriptionState** (delta_subscription_state.h) with DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory: Handles Delta protocol state\n\nBoth inherit from **BaseSubscriptionState** (subscription_state.h), a template class that provides common xDS-over-gRPC protocol handling.\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\n\n**GrpcMuxContext** (grpc_mux_context.h): Configuration context passed to mux implementations containing async client, dispatcher, service method, local info, rate limiting settings, etc.\n\n**GrpcMuxFailover** (grpc_mux_failover.h): Multiplexes streams between primary and failover xDS sources.\n\n**GrpcStream** (grpc_stream.h): Manages the gRPC stream lifecycle and message sending.\n\n**WatchMap** (watch_map.h): Tracks watches/subscriptions per resource type and manages subscription state transitions.\n\n**PausableAckQueue** (pausable_ack_queue.h): Queues ACKs/NACKs with pause/resume capability for rate limiting.\n\nThe factory pattern enables runtime selection between SotW and Delta modes, with the newer unified template architecture providing better code reuse and maintainability for both protocols."
}

